-- Lincoln National explores sale of unit: WSJ
-- 
-- Thu Apr 26, 2007 4:13am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/26/us-lincoln-unit-sale-idUSN2634093720070426

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Life insurer Lincoln National Corp. ( LNC.N ) is in the process of hiring advisers for a potential sale of its broadcast and media unit, the Wall Street Journal reported on its Web site on Thursday. 

 The unit might be worth about $1.5 billion, the paper said, citing unnamed sources. Lincoln could not immediately be reached for comment.